Raliegh Riddoch (CRD# 3066175) 
Raliegh is a managing principal of BSW Wealth Partners and an Advisor. It’s Raliegh’s role to help clients find appropriate solutions for many of the complex financial situations they encounter. Over the years, he has learned that he adds the most value by helping clients find the balance between the quantitative and qualitative pieces that make up their lives. Since 1998, Raliegh has spent time advising clients on a wide range of financial matters while working for firms such as: TD Waterhouse, Charles Schwab, and Dain Rauscher. The combination of his investment experience and passion for offering objective financial advice brought him to Baydush Simon Weaver in 2005. He is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ professional as well as a Certified Divorce Financial Analyst®. He is also a member of the Financial Planning Association and The Institute for Divorce Financial Analysts (IDFA™).
In 1997, he earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Finance from the Monfort Business School, at the University of Northern Colorado.
Although spending time with his wife Kristi and daughters Gwendolynn and Adliegh is his favorite pastime, he also enjoys athletics and playing in Colorado’s great outdoors.
